    simulation

    Generate a sequence of G values

    generate_sequence.Rd

    Generate a sequence of G values based on the specified parameters.

    Usage

    generate_sequence(phi, lambda, eta)

    Arguments

    phi

    A numeric value representing the correlation parameter between two contious observations.

    lambda

    A numeric value representing the place where chang point happens.

    eta

    A numeric value representing the constants when generating 'yt' based on 'xt'.

    Value

    A vector of G values.

    Examples

    generate_sequence(phi = 0.5, lambda = 0.2, eta = 1)
#>  [1] 20.074508 13.726827 31.607955  2.591526  2.818693  8.596335  2.757768
